Annotation Interface CanIgnoreReturnValue

@Documented @Target({METHOD,CONSTRUCTOR,TYPE}) @Retention(CLASS) public @interface CanIgnoreReturnValue
Indicates that the return value of the annotated API is ignorable.

This is the opposite of CheckReturnValue. It can be used inside classes or packages annotated with @CheckReturnValue to exempt specific APIs from the default.
